	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Durban - A 40 year-old cyclist died after attempts to save his life failed in Westville on Friday, paramedics said. ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing said a passerby saw the man lying on Methven road. The woman began CPR on the man. “ER24 paramedics as well as other services attended to the incident and took over CPR,” Bodasing said. Events leading up to the man being found lying on the road were unknown. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  